div.p:
TO passe by the two Bils brought into the House of Commons, for taking away Bishops, root and branch;
               Two Bills about Bishops and the Militia, Stusb. 251.543, Tumults in Ian, & Decemb, 1641.
               and for taking the Militia from the King, and setling it in other hands: (both which Bils were rejected in a full and free Convention of Parliament) Also to passe by the Tumults raised in December and Ianuary 1041. For reviving and carrying on the Bils before rejected, by driving away the dissenting Members, and new moulding the two Houses of Parliament.
